Stars: 1. I love 8bit games and I have been in search of Japanese traditional looking game so this is great! 2. The Combos are fun to recreate (of course, I used wikifandom) 3. The music is somehow not tiring to hear. üòÇ Most of the games like these have super repetitive music that you get sick of, this one did not have that effect on me. 4. I really root for my people in the end, my favorite is Akindo! He excels at everything! Wish: 1. I wish that it I could've transfer my Lite version to Full.

Edo Towns has to be one of my favorite Kairosoft games. I love the graphics, I think the game itself is quite entertaining and challenging.  However, I thought the game could have been better with more options such as character interaction and customization also with the terrain as well, it bothered me that I could not remove the hills but having more control of the design of your own town would have been better.  What would have really been was being able to expand your town as well but besides all of the I still think Edo Towns is great for what it is if.
One of my favourite Kairosoft games. Keep going back to play. The newer releases are nothing compared to the older games.

It's quite fun.  Hard to earn money,  and  it's nothing like the other pixel where they grow old- but not this game.  It's like their time are frozen,  the life was a cycle with a bit of changes. Was it fun?  Yes Was it satisfying?  Nope Should i refund?  Yep,  obviously no  refund once u played them so far.  Was it worth to spend?  Kind of Should I suggest you buy this game?  Depends,  If you have a long patience and if  u don't mind them "not" growing old.
Gooddd

Overall this game is really cute and amazing but I feel like there could have been more content and detail to the village and villagers. Like it sucks that you can only place buildings in two directions or the fact that you can't move a building or house to a different location it just gets deleted. Last thing it would be cute if the villagers aged or fell in love like Dream Days. Like I said its a very enjoyable game with loads of play time and you won't get bored

I love city sims, and I love Kairosoft. They didn't disappoint. This is probably my favorite of the 7-8 KS games I've played. It makes the other sims on the market worthless, especially the wack free ones. Only complaints: there's no industry, and no employment model like in Epic Astro. The only tile that requires a worker is farms; other than that, you can have a million shops and zero houses as far as I can tell. KS missed a big opportunity there to give the game more depth and therefore to last longer.
